        "subject": "LU-4800 utils: do explicit modprobe when module autoload fails",
        "message": "LU-4800 utils: do explicit modprobe when module autoload fails\n\nFailure of the usual kernel module autoload mechanism has been\nobserved multiple times.  Frequently seen at mount time during\nlustre client mounts with newer linux kernel versions.\nThis fix does an explict modprobe to force loading lustre kernel\nmodules.\n\nSigned-off-by: Bob Glossman <bob.glossman@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I14508f5ddadf5e5ef3866f72c66ebb0335aec909\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
